Granted, class I took was online, so maybe the in-class experience with Fletcher is very different. However, the online course is extremely heavy in readings, graded off 2 midterms 1 final, and is mundane/rambling in her lectures, with minimal engaging material/visual aid. Essay questions are poorly structured, confusing, and ridiculously long

rComments: I took Kate for CRM 2306 and she is by far the best crim prof at uottawa. You must attend lectures as her slides are pretty empty and you have to do the readings in order to pass. i really love kate - i think we're soulmates. sis really did throw me for a loop though with the 2nd midterm - waaaaay too much to write in 1.5 hours. if you don't do the readings you will fail the course

Kate Fletcher is one of the best professors I have had in my 2 years here at Ottawa U, she is very passionate about what she teaches and pushes students to strive for their best. Kate is awesome. I have had her a couple of times and I would recommend her to anyone. You must attend class but she makes the lectures very interesting. I've taken two classes with Kate and am hoping to take more! She is very clear about her expectations and gives great feedback. Her lectures often explore critical and debatable topics, it makes the class very interesting and informative.

Kate does an excellent job of conveying important information. Kate is always looking for ways to help students succeed, she truly has students best interest in mind. I look forward to taking more classes with her in the future. Excellent professor, one of the best.

rComments: Get ready to really learn! I loved this class. It was really interactive, with an opportunity to be introspective and critical of the material in the essays. The lectures are important because she uses them to highlight keys points and unpack the dense information in the mandatory article readings. She doesn't post any lectures online.

Kate is hands down one of the best profs I've ever had. You can tell that she loves what she does and knows what she's talking about. Her lectures are very interesting and are worth going to. Her readings are kinda long and her midterms are always papers and always a take-home final. Would def take her every semester if I could!

Kate is one of the best profs I've ever had. Her material is very interesting and it shows she knows what she's talking about. Kate is one of the best profs I have had, she is incredibly helpful and actually takes the time to get to know names. Her lectures are very interactive and loves when students participate. She clearly knows what she is talking about and makes an effort to make sure the subject is comprehended.

Best prof I have had at uOttawa! Truly cares about her students and will always meet up with anyone to answer any questions :)
Best professor I've had to date at UOttawa!

One of the best professors I had at uOttawa! Definitely Recommend.

Professor Fletcher is such an amazing person. She really cares about the students who are interested in learning the material she has to teach.
